The paper discusses a scheme for eavesdropping on a secure key distribution system, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The analysis of the cracking scheme involves statistical methods and signal processing, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses potential experimental artifacts, which could be relevant to physics (cs.PH).
